# Swagger/OpenAPI Documentation Rule

## Overview
Implement Swagger/OpenAPI documentation using Echo-Swagger for automatic API documentation generation, interactive API explorer, and comprehensive endpoint documentation.

## Framework Choice
- **Echo-Swagger**: Official Swagger integration for Echo framework
- **Swag**: Go code annotations for automatic Swagger generation
- **Benefits**: Auto-generated docs, interactive explorer, code-first approach

## Directory Structure
```
internal/presentation/http/
├── docs/                    # Generated Swagger documentation
│   ├── docs.go             # Auto-generated docs
│   ├── swagger.json        # OpenAPI specification
│   └── swagger.yaml        # OpenAPI specification (YAML)
├── server.go               # Server with Swagger setup
├── handler/                # HTTP handlers with Swagger annotations
└── .cursor/rules/          # Rules directory
    └── swagger.mdc         # This rule file
```

## Installation

### Dependencies
```bash
# Install Echo-Swagger
go get github.com/swaggo/echo-swagger

# Install Swag CLI for code generation
go install github.com/swaggo/swag/cmd/swag@latest

# Install Swagger UI assets
go get github.com/swaggo/files
```

